          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_QLcIRZwnEfC2s4m-Mpzytw" annotatedElement="_QLcIRJwnEfC2s4m-Mpzytw">
            <body>Indicates whether the Local PTP Clock is used for timestamping PTP event messages in order to compute the PTP Telecom Profile Instance performance monitoring statistics.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to True, the Local PTP Clock is used for timestamping PTP event messages.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to False, the Local PTP Clock is not used for timestamping PTP event messages.&#xD;
&#xD;
Editors' Note: Pending confirmation with Q13/15 that the isInvariant is false.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
      </packagedElement>
      <packagedElement xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" xmi:id="_T92ZoJ46EfCL-5b_aa81hQ" name="Timestamp">
        <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_cgRtsJ46EfCL-5b_aa81hQ" annotatedElement="_T92ZoJ46EfCL-5b_aa81hQ">
          <body>The timestamp at which a specific event happens.&#xD;
&#xD;
Each data modelling language can utilize a different data type for storing the time of the monitoring information.&#xD;
&#xD;
Editors' Note: To be replaced by a common UML data type (e.g., from TCIM).</body>
        </ownedComment>
      </packagedElement>
