          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#String"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_t8lPoMB-Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" name="portType" type="_zSI_EMB-Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" isReadOnly="true">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_5OQiwMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" annotatedElement="_t8lPoMB-Ee6csOUPxtf2vA">
            <body>The type of the SyncPhy Port.</body>
          </ownedComment>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_OK9boMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" name="portStatus" type="_mQHdwMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" isReadOnly="true">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_8Mw7QMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" annotatedElement="_OK9boMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA">
            <body>The status of the SyncPhy Port.</body>
          </ownedComment>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_Rtcq8MB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" name="lockOut">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_EBKrsMCAEe6csOUPxtf2vA" annotatedElement="_Rtcq8MB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA">
            <body>The configuration of the Lockout function of the SyncPhy Port.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the SyncPhy Port is able to be considered by the selection process.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the SyncPhy Port is no longer considered by the selection process.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_UNtoQMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" name="ssmSupp">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_WA8rAMCAEe6csOUPxtf2vA" annotatedElement="_UNtoQMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA">
            <body>Indicates whether a SyncPhy Port is configured to process the received Synchronization Status Message (SSM).&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the SyncPhy Port is configured not to process the received SSM.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the SyncPhy Port is configured to process the received SSM.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
          <lowerValue xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger" xmi:id="_qOLnkAZtEfCYoadliKChew"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_XJom0MB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" name="eSsmSupp" isReadOnly="true">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_zn5hwMCAEe6csOUPxtf2vA" annotatedElement="_XJom0MB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA">
            <body>Indicates whether a SyncPhy Port supports the ability to process the received enhanced Synchronization Status Message (eSSM).&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the SyncPhy Port cannot support the ability to process the received eSSM.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the SyncPhy Port supports the ability to process the received eSSM.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_Z6IYgMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA" name="localPriorityForSystemClock">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_G2uHEMCBEe6csOUPxtf2vA" annotatedElement="_Z6IYgMB_Ee6csOUPxtf2vA">
            <body>The priority of the SyncPhy Port that is a candidate reference for the system clock (see the selection process 1 in Figure 5-6 and Selector B in Figure A.2).&#xD;
&#xD;
A smaller number has a higher priority.&#xD;
&#xD;
The value 0 represents that this SyncPhy Portis not nominated for the system clock.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Integer"/>
          <defaultValue xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger" xmi:id="_mPpHYAfLEfCVfpmBxw8Ozw"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_L3xaQL99Ee6xirORnB-xqg" name="ssmSendEnable">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_L3xaQb99Ee6xirORnB-xqg" annotatedElement="_L3xaQL99Ee6xirORnB-xqg">
            <body>Indicates whether the SyncPhy Portis required to send Synchronization Status Message (SSM) messages.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the SyncPhy Port is not allowed to send SSM messages.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the SyncPhy Port is required to send SSM messages.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
