          <body>The additional Default data set (DS) members of the PTP Telecom Profile Instance in an end application with local time reference (LTR).</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_L5t-AC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" name="withLtr" isReadOnly="true">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_yOLXcC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" annotatedElement="_L5t-AC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ">
            <body>Reports whether the end application has a local time reference (LTR) or not.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the end application has an LTR.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the end application does not have an LTR.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
          <lowerValue xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger" xmi:id="_qTdjoC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_OfxaQC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" name="ltrValid" isReadOnly="true">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_9DNnUC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" annotatedElement="_OfxaQC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ">
            <body>Reports whether the local time reference (LTR) status of the end application is valid or invalid.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the LTR status is valid.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the LTR status is invalid.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
          <lowerValue xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger" xmi:id="_1sYjsC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_QwEo8C3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" name="timeStatus" isReadOnly="true">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_HsZzkC3sEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" annotatedElement="_QwEo8C3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ">
            <body>Reports whether the time of the end application is normal or not.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the time is normal (e.g., there is no clock alarm).&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the time is unnormal (e.g., the time offset calculated by the active reference is not stable).</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
          <lowerValue xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger" xmi:id="_CbQDAC3sEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_So2IcC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" name="ptpReference" isReadOnly="true">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_QkeAcC3sEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" annotatedElement="_So2IcC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ">
            <body>The active time reference of the end application.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to TRUE, the active time reference is PTP.&#xD;
&#xD;
When set to FALSE, the active time reference is the local time reference (LTR).</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Boolean"/>
          <lowerValue xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger" xmi:id="_Lf23EC3sEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Property" xmi:id="_VBI1gC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" name="messageInterval">
          <ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="_dDrTIC3sEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ" annotatedElement="_VBI1gC3rEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ">
            <body>The Signaling message interval as the interval of the Signaling message sent by the end application.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/UMLPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#Integer"/>
          <lowerValue xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger" xmi:id="_ViMesC3sEfGX7Jwr7U0FeQ"/>
        </ownedAttribute>
      </packagedElement>
